# svelte-supabase-auth-template

Read **`INSTRUCTIONS.md`** first — Supabase project, Google Cloud OAuth app, Supabase Google provider, redirect URLs, and `.env.local` are required before the app works in production.

- Feature contract: `index.md`
- Agent skills: `.agents/skills/README.md`
- Routes: `/`, `/login`, `/signup`, `/recover-password`, `/reset-password`
- API client: `src/lib/api.ts` (`apiFetch`) → worker at `VITE_API_BASE_URL`
- Auth state: `src/lib/auth.ts` (writable stores + `initAuth`)
- Router: `src/routes.ts` (`svelte-spa-router` + `wrap` conditions)

Auth is Supabase-only on the client; domain API calls go to the worker, not `supabase.from()` for app data.

Pairing backend (not in this repo): [cf-hono-supabase-api-template](https://github.com/open-templates/cf-hono-supabase-api-template) — same Supabase project; worker `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` must include this app's origin.
